options.content: AWS Elemental MediaLive
To generate traffic, open our Live Big Buck Bunny stream.

panels.description: The total number of alerts that are active.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  concat('Pipeline #', labels['Pipeline']) AS "Pipeline", value['max'] AS "Active Alerts Count"
FROM
  ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
WHERE metric_name = 'ActiveAlerts'
  AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
  AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
  AND $__conditionalAll(labels['Pipeline'] IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
  AND timestamp = (
      SELECT max(timestamp)
      FROM ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
      WHERE metric_name = 'ActiveAlerts'
      AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
  )
ORDER by "Pipeline" ASC

panels.title: Active Alerts

panels.description: The number of outputs that are being produced and successfully written to the destination.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  labels['OutputGroupName'] AS "Group Name", labels['Pipeline'] AS "Pipeline", value['min'] AS "Active"
FROM
  ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
WHERE metric_name = 'ActiveOutputs'
  AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
  AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
  AND $__conditionalAll(labels['Pipeline'] IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
  AND timestamp = (
      SELECT addMinutes(max(timestamp), -1)
      FROM ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
      WHERE metric_name = 'ActiveOutputs'
      AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
  )
ORDER BY "Group Name" ASC, "Pipeline" ASC

panels.title: Active Outputs

panels.description: The number of 5xx HTTP errors that have been received from the destination while delivering output.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, value['sum'] AS "Output 5xx Errors"
FROM
  ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
WHERE metric_name = 'Output5xxErrors'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
AND $__conditionalAll(labels['Pipeline'] IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC

panels.title: Output 4xx Errors

panels.description: This metric is an indicator of the health of the input. If the value isn't stable, investigate determine if there are problems with your source, and/or problems in the network between MediaLive and the upstream system.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, concat('Pipeline #', labels['Pipeline']) AS "Pipeline", value['max'] AS "Max Input Video Frame Rate"
FROM
  ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
WHERE metric_name = 'InputVideoFrameRate'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
AND $__conditionalAll(labels['Pipeline'] IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Pipeline" ASC

panels.title: Input Video Frame Rate

panels.description: The number of input frames that MediaLive has dropped in the period. A value of 0 is expected and indicates that MediaLive is processing incoming frames in real time. A value other than 0 indicates that the encoder can't process the incoming video fast enough to keep up with real time.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, concat('Pipeline #', labels['Pipeline']) AS "Pipeline", value['sum'] AS "Sum Dropped Frames"
FROM
  ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
WHERE metric_name = 'DroppedFrames'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
AND $__conditionalAll(labels['Pipeline'] IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Pipeline" ASC

panels.title: Dropped Frames

panels.description: The percentage of time that MediaLive has had to reduce quality optimizations in order to emit output in real time. SVQ stands for speed versus quality. Any encoding task must balance emitting output in real time against a desire to produce the best quality possible. But sometimes MediaLive must reduce quality in order to encode fast enough to keep up with real time.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, concat('Pipeline #', labels['Pipeline']) AS "Pipeline", value['max'] AS " "
FROM
  ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
WHERE metric_name = 'SvqTime'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
AND $__conditionalAll(labels['Pipeline'] IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Pipeline" ASC

panels.title: SVQ Time

panels.description: The current length of time (the fill period) during which MediaLive has filled the video output with fill frames. The fill period starts when the pipeline does not receive content from the input within the expected time. The expected time is based on the input frame rate. The fine points of the fill frame behavior are controlled by the input loss behavior fields in the channel configuration.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, concat('Pipeline #', labels['Pipeline']) AS "Pipeline", value['max'] AS " "
FROM
  ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
WHERE metric_name = 'FillMsec'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
AND $__conditionalAll(labels['Pipeline'] IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Pipeline" ASC

panels.title: Fill Msec

panels.description: The rate of traffic coming into MediaLive. This number includes all traffic received into MediaLive—push inputs, pull inputs, responses from the upstream system of a pull input, responses from the downstream system for any output, and instance traffic such as DNS resolution and NTP. Even when a channel is not ingesting, there will be some traffic.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, concat('Pipeline #', labels['Pipeline']) AS "Pipeline", value['sum']/value['count'] AS "Rate Network In"
FROM
  ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
WHERE metric_name = 'NetworkIn'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
AND $__conditionalAll(labels['Pipeline'] IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Pipeline" ASC

panels.title: Network In (Mbps)

panels.description: The rate of traffic out of MediaLive. This number includes all traffic sent from MediaLive — the media output, HTTP GET requests for pull inputs, NTP traffic, and DNS traffic. Even when a channel is not delivering output, there will be some traffic.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, concat('Pipeline #', labels['Pipeline']) AS "Pipeline", value['sum']/value['count'] AS " "
FROM
  ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveMetricsTbl}
WHERE metric_name = 'NetworkOut'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ChannelId'] = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
AND $__conditionalAll(labels['Pipeline'] IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, "Pipeline" ASC

panels.title: Output 4xx Errors

targets.rawSql:
SELECT timestamp, concat(channel_id, ' - ', toString(encoder_pipeline), ' - ', message) AS "log_message", level, channel_id, encoder_pipeline, message
FROM ${v_HdxProject}.${v_HdxMediaLiveEncoderLogsTbl}
WHERE 
  account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
  AND channel_id = '${v_MediaLive_ChannelId}'
  AND $__conditionalAll(encoder_pipeline IN (${v_MediaLive_Pipeline}), ${v_MediaLive_Pipeline})
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC
